\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Main results. (a)\nonbreakingspace Rank IC increases with horizon, consistent with drift SNR $\propto \sqrt  {h}$. (b)\nonbreakingspace Long-short cumulative returns under different cost assumptions. (c)\nonbreakingspace Decile portfolio returns exhibit perfect monotonicity. (d)\nonbreakingspace Phantom's IC dominates all simple baselines; the low-volatility strategy is the strongest competitor.}}{6}{figure.caption.19}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:main}{{2}{6}{Main results. (a)~Rank IC increases with horizon, consistent with drift SNR $\propto \sqrt {h}$. (b)~Long-short cumulative returns under different cost assumptions. (c)~Decile portfolio returns exhibit perfect monotonicity. (d)~Phantom's IC dominates all simple baselines; the low-volatility strategy is the strongest competitor}{figure.caption.19}{}}
